                            <comment id="13575940" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 11 Feb 2013 18:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I can tell, this was fixed as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-442&quot; title=&quot;StringIndexOutOfBoundsException: String index out of range: -1 if server respond with root is current directory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NET-442&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NET-442&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is included in NET 3.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There does not seem to be a problem with the current code, see:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;URL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1444907&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1444907&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Log:&lt;br/&gt;
Add test for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-502&quot; title=&quot;Apache FTPClient doesn&amp;#39;t handle common responses to PWD&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NET-502&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NET-502&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modified:&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/net/trunk/src/test/java/org/apache/commons/net/ftp/FTPClientTest.java&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Please provide a test case that shows the problem.&lt;br/&gt;
For example, as a patch for FTPClientTest.java.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13575974" author="barrkel" created="Mon, 11 Feb 2013 19:00:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmmm; it looks like &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1420655&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1420655&lt;/a&gt; fixed it, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-492&quot; title=&quot;FTPClient.printWorkingDirectory() incorrectly parses certain valid PWD command results&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NET-492&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NET-492&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; rather than &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-442&quot; title=&quot;StringIndexOutOfBoundsException: String index out of range: -1 if server respond with root is current directory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NET-442&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NET-442&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13686865" author="cerker" created="Tue, 18 Jun 2013 16:04:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Barry is right, in &lt;br/&gt;
  end = lastIndexOf(&quot;\&quot; &quot;), &lt;br/&gt;
there was a space after the double quote, so for a valid response like &apos;257 &quot;/&quot;&apos;, the result was &apos;&quot;/&quot;&apos; instead of &apos;/&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I stumbled upon this using the current Camel version 2.11.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
